g.text: Nettie leads the player into a lab and fetches a thorn. The player doesn't know, but the thorn is a deadly poison. Nettie knows it's the only choice she has - the player could transform into a monster and kill everyone in the camp. She sees this as a kindness - the transformation is terrible - so she has a very 'matter of fact nurse' tone about the whole thing before she scratches you, but will get stressed if you resist. Once she's scratched the player, her tone will be softer - kinder. She plans to sit with you while you pass and make it as easy as possible. The player will have to convince her they're not a threat if they're going to get the antidote. She'll be slow to convince, hesitant to allow any risk to the camp.

g.title: n08bbe928b263ca8f14786318be4a5c24
g.text: This one had the same problem as you. Attacked us in the woods together with some goblins.

g.title: n00465ffcdaf7ada3db2f3acb44088a4a
g.text: Same as the drow... But Master Halsin said he'd turn eventually.

g.title: n020343575d6819b1d8e761cc8e60c636
g.text: The door's locked. Neither of us are leaving until this is done.

g.title: n04e2704ef560a8442cdf7de0c2d878ce
g.text: I swear, by the Lord of Justice.

g.title: n33950ac7f1cb6c553ba2868d517964d8
g.text: Thank you. I truly hope it doesn't come to that.

g.title: n7e709ac284046e90ebbfd612de50cd83
g.text: I hope it doesn't come to that but... thank you. Here.

g.title: n899226cefbff803327fd880b4f28ff25
g.text: We can look after our own. Starting with this.

g.title: na68cea658e9e39e9807a4d7b6123b6c2
g.text: He attacked Master Halsin and I in the woods, leading a pack of goblins.

g.title: ne5c46fef838e1275b4f65d301ca9dc93
g.text: *You try to dodge her blow, but she catches you, scratching your hand.*

g.title: n091249dad5485aac855ad6b767690d04
g.text: I respect Kagha, but she can't order me to put everyone's lives at risk.

g.title: n51e2734f3badd3aea9437abdfc2f2887
g.text: I'm sorry. There's nothing you can say to change my mind.

g.title: na980670457a67ef87f803d0c57d446e0
g.text: A pity you got me instead of him. He spent days studying the drow's tadpole - maybe he found an easier way. Still...

g.title: nda5e527949658388a7a0c5ff99ae2b1e
g.text: I swear, by the Lord of Justice.

g.title: n144ec78d682d7cac58bedf7ae105b6c0
g.text: You - you're right. I'm no use to the others dead.

g.title: nb02972e344f56fda4ce70d3b709b487d
g.text: Master Halsin did said the drow's tadpole was dormant. Maybe yours is too.

g.title: n1563ada4e907771b16e5fe20d6fc4eca
g.text: Exactly! I'm glad you're coming to your senses.

g.title: n15c5a08241e996ab023d0a62b2cad022
g.text: I know you're not changing yet - and I've no idea why not - but we have to assume it's only a matter of time.

g.title: n926b80ba875d52aa59040ed29c67ecc3
g.text: You must understand you are in grave danger. You have to find Master Halsin. He might be your only chance.

g.title: n17502d9fb53e4f24241502d9d2ee1346
g.text: I'm truly, truly sorry. For what it's worth, the poison is painless. It'll be like going to sleep.

g.title: n82bd76f8c65a36fe30e2453e908a162f
g.text: I know where Halsin is! Give me the antidote or he'll die too.

g.title: n185482ad23b507944fb6b2bad5cd91de
g.text: All right! Master Halsin did say the drow's tadpole was dormant. Maybe yours is too.

g.title: n38e9f34063636ef8d7f016a44298161e
g.text: But first - this is a vial of wyvern poison. Swear to me you'll swallow it if you feel

g.title: nab14e6c187820aeb548af7eb01abf0aa
g.text: But first, swear to me you'll do what needs to be done.

g.title: n1b09988692ec90ba74592f4de87e892f
g.text: As long as there's a chance, you're not saving me. You're commiting murder.

g.title: nebf45504d55c7f2b05f3df80de863c50
g.text: I understand you're angry, I really do, but I won't let you endanger these people.

g.title: n1c3fec48ee7bb5e0c9882f8b75d1eae1
g.text: I don't want it. This was a mistake.

g.title: nc59c285d29c0a0cb075901ccd85a6a32
g.text: No! I can't let you leave - you could transform any second.

g.title: n1c470fd7fff02ec82b04fc97b9a68007
g.text: I know where Halsin is! I can save him, but only if you let me go.

g.title: n1d4777b55a7a8142f628bd004b807c2f
g.text: Give me the antidote or I'll break you in two.

g.title: n1f78988b99fb99232fdd44ba7044cdda
g.text: No. I'm not taking poison from a woman I can't trust.

g.title: ndb19b214ebd33e0fae42d3a909025b5c
g.text: Then I've no choice. I'm sorry.

g.title: n207d75609e41da161a8dabac23cb9b9c
g.text: Wait, my legs? What kind of cure is this?

g.title: n4ba673fe019a6705a949f7fa9dc97986
g.text: I'm sorry. Maybe Master Halsin could have plucked it from your head, but I can't.

g.title: n21eeeb5bb9ae5db995b67e21033bdda2
g.text: I won't turn into one of them.

g.title: ne8c4ed4cba0120962827161eb8cb9d2c
g.text: Same as the drow... But Master Halsin said he'd turn eventually.

g.title: n2299895a57bcd5426681921c7261dc88
g.text: Is everyone being captured by mind flayers these days? Didn't think it was a common experience.

g.title: n2b1d6745b693e667ce7138ade8ce6393
g.text: What in the hells have you done?

g.title: n3260decf6e3d63fa82faefe6cab85d8b
g.text: Don't be a fool. I'd kill you before you could blink.

g.title: n84cca1d3fbd22a0570d885fc51b64506
g.text: Dodge when she lunges for you.

g.title: nea70d2d7689615cb1d5ce9934015105e
g.text: Attack her first - kill her quickly.

g.title: n2d5c1919702de7eadead751247789d2b
g.text: Please, don't mind me. I'll just watch.

g.title: n3208725a019489831555551bdf636cf1
g.text: Then I'm sorry, but I can't. You're too dangerous.

g.title: n759d3c800ab3aa4b96c89490177398f5
g.text: By rights your teeth should be falling out and your skin turning grey. I don't know why you haven't changed, but I can't risk you suddenly turning into a mind flayer.

g.title: n3421d85c487bea49976f14648c1e129f
g.text: Do you know where he is?

g.title: n67ff26ef1dc07e0ba7e0f33f2e5d4754
g.text: Ask the adventurers that abandoned him. They're the only ones who know what really happened out there.

g.title: na286d6fa7d84b62c24e7eeaa5e8a56cd
g.text: No. He left with that adventuring party, but I couldn't tell you what happened out there.

g.title: n34de22c4eebbc4886d700d6ad5667fda
g.text: I'm hoping for a less grave cure.

g.title: n4cfe607d44e6aa44d1cce12482ee3984
g.text: I'll do the best I can.

g.title: n368e3a21c5123333c2d7fbc2b52fb53f
g.text: I'm the only one that can find Halsin.

g.title: n36dafd8d9f332c4e61da4f4346d23577
g.text: Give me the antidote or I'll break you in two.

g.title: n36dee272d57d6504877fdef6dab448e5
g.text: You can't hit me, let alone kill me. Don't make me put you down.

g.title: n3785e6254c3b2d8644b79ed7c7e6f534
g.text: *She doesn't hesitate, moving quickly. Before you realise what's happening, you feel a burning scratch on your hand.*

g.title: n3acaa34160c45f87907af8a66e284ece
g.text: It's too late. It's already in your system.

g.title: n3c069d76130724b23dd0db3525c0b1f8
g.text: Thank you. I truly hope it doesn't come to that.

g.title: n8081ba3ce42fbff27f6239dbb99f963a
g.text: Here, take this. It'll stop the poison, but I can't do anything for that wriggler in your head.

g.title: nd556b9ad6e5fa517087b97cdb56cad75
g.text: Now, I've an antidote - um ... where is the bloody thing?

g.title: n3d4622b6e6cb20d7c30a8c4ce28cd66d
g.text: I understand you're angry, I really do, but I won't let you endanger these people.

g.title: n3e805eddbd685b096b10acbd0755e360
g.text: The drow was leading a gang of goblins. Not a common pairing.

g.title: n80c122876c662ee9972d7d3ce678e3bc
g.text: They attacked us - we had to defend ourselves. It's only after, when we saw the tadpole crawling out of his head, that Master Halsin realised how serious things were.

g.title: n3fb319d60d5fad78fe9c93d42b4cec9f
g.text: You said I have time - let me use it.

g.title: n422e327b85d9326740b46f6dd9cd0559
g.text: I'm safe - I'm not showing symptoms, and it's been days.

g.title: n4326f5f070937207642d3035bf9189e1
g.text: You can't do this - your leader needs to talk to me.

g.title: n62ad4be13c3fefac44deba8cd2a568a3
g.text: Please, try to relax. This doesn't have to be hard.

g.title: nd005442f4aca687b2d23d0b321cdcc75
g.text: Be careful. Your legs'll probably give out first.

g.title: n6077d97e74e81e8db9f8727a49ebc785
g.text: *You dodge her blow, but as you regain your footing you can see the pain in her eyes.*

g.title: ne31d36a2340b0a78345157dce0d1b880
g.text: Without him here, the only treatment for an illithid tadpole is death. You're a risk to the people around you.

g.title: nc5eb2d077a265487bd5832296443a1ea
g.text: I'm no Master Halsin, mind. He'd have your tadpole out like that. Still, we have options.

g.title: n4f5eee9aea91015c7b7efc42d0806fbc
g.text: I have important information - your grove will die without it.

g.title: n8a9b720855b96ec716b6d066d7bc131f
g.text: I respect Kagha, but she can't order me to put everyone's lives at risk.

g.title: nb63ec106afaf977ff639700295eee78e
g.text: I - I'm sorry, but I can't let you go.

g.title: n5e44b5739298089087998367944411b3
g.text: Well, not to worry. Have a read of that book -
. There's a recipe for your antidote in there.

g.title: n78e3ae6214b67bdc25d861fcc9ab1bb3
g.text: It's no cure, though, and it's a miracle you're not changing already. I can't say why your skin isn't turning grey and your teeth dropping out, but it's only a matter of time.

g.title: ndad8597c863b9ad462cf5d9097dc95e3
g.text: I'm sorry, I truly am, but I can't let you go.

g.title: n62197c37e6b7977fc02d2596d0fbfba8
g.text: So I have time? There's a chance.

g.title: nbba17a7ce2c5df3c36672313d7a37715
g.text: All I know is they went to the old temple of Selne and he didn't make it back.

g.title: n68ab3823f82a68cf0a51a6786522e5b6
g.text: I will remain. I've a vested interest in the outcome.

g.title: n6921c663691676e4e4673ef3f3024595
g.text: Swear to me that if you feel

g.title: n6cdbc78957bb846cf47560658f23e403
g.text: I won't turn into one of them.

g.title: na25707fb5d87011da31262db83a6c69a
g.text: Are you mad? I'm not going to kill myself - symptoms or not.

g.title: n6a465c43eac65e0ff9d3be93f0ce1463
g.text: This is a vial of wyvern poison. Swear to me you'll swallow it if you feel

g.title: n6d6cf24c3216ca524060b00679378458
g.text: Rather too common as of late. At least that's what Master Halsin suspected. It's why he joined the adventurers on their expedition.

g.title: n6e66be36d45f05059832b8a99abd6b4a
g.text: I hope it doesn't come to that but... thank you. Here.

g.title: nfa165e8dafcb029a3b2ed7e6ff65ecba
g.text: And here's the antidote. Do not mix those two up.

g.title: n6ec9b02dc888e0f1baceb84b723c220f
g.text: No one else can stop those goblins. You need me.

g.title: n6f127d1477212bbdc7d0cc4714c84e81
g.text: Did you kill that drow because he was going to turn?

g.title: nb56b8484dec6b09a836363b0a651bbae
g.text: Oh no, he would've slit me navel to nape if Master Halsin hadn't put him down.

g.title: n6f57425ed3094ad3343e24f7e39697e9
g.text: You came to me for help. Do you want it or not?

g.title: n71558c1b0565f6fc10a7eaabd5223aab
g.text: This is the last time I'll ask.

g.title: ndbe4fff51827cf22f6066c44e32ebd75
g.text: You're not asking. This is a threat.

g.title: n9c55473555379682e86310dbc7822b13
g.text: Do whatever you need to, but we're not leaving this room until it's over.

g.title: n76550b3206ab9e732a613639e0da92dc
g.text: Now, your arm, please. You don't have time for games.

g.title: nd47fc1ae8a9289afa19dde8707a7f535
g.text: Are you mad? I'm not going to kill myself - symptoms or not.

g.title: nf34a35e3afc00e23a792b76c0db0beea
g.text: You're not getting out of here. I'll do whatever I have to to protect my kin.

g.title: nbabc33519152fed6e82db20d72c2385f
g.text: And by rights, you should already be changing. Greying skin, teeth falling out - you should've gone through it all. Though maybe it's only a matter of time.

g.title: nc31fd7d66c66606ec0567b2470dc1568
g.text: Hells' teeth, why didn't you say anything sooner? I'll tell you where the antidote is, but there's a condition.

g.title: n84cfeb5a76f7378b72b26a52771f25e2
g.text: The door's locked. Neither of us are leaving until this is done.

g.title: n8791af9e8ef568ff93e4e72037e848c8
g.text: If you transform out there, you'll kill everyone in the grove. Everyone for leagues around.

g.title: n95cc0ad007b8daaf1c3197027adad433
g.text: I'm not showing symptoms - I have time.

g.title: nc41440ca69465f6e0fe83f0fb14d685e
g.text: I'm immune - I just want the tadpole gone to be safe.

g.title: n8e98c147a9ff5168702ec0ee6ee8ca88
g.text: This is a vial of wyvern poison. Swear to me you'll swallow it if you feel

g.title: n8e9ac95875741dbe72394f1fdb764a74
g.text: I'm interested in the procedure actually. Please, go ahead.

g.title: n8fcc76eb7b1295c7f3ddcb3e9ffab39f
g.text: The poison might kill me, but not before I tear this grove apart looking for the cure.

g.title: n92670ed2046c1da371bc65279c8edb84
g.text: Remember what I said. Remember your oath!

g.title: n9b874f5a873354d906d35fc0f8f52743
g.text: What makes you so sure Halsin can help me?

g.title: n9b20f251402b8858ccf7fd56999f3678
g.text: I just want a chance to find a cure.

g.title: nac28ac1a5de93596f31d95ed4ba7d5a7
g.text: Master Halsin's a renowned healer. He studied the drow's tadpole for days and concluded he needed to find the source of the infection to understand its nature.

g.title: nae221b055cb62221e84ec3845e80ce28
g.text: No, I'll stay. I'd rather know exactly what you're up to.

g.title: nc97f1876735403097b250f0f6680d314
g.text: I'll hang around, if it's all the same.

g.title: naf3f0888097176156728e099c49539c6
g.text: Tadpole crawled out of his head soon after.

g.title: na72d0e72dec7a6b8d3c12a7b4ca14afc
g.text: You can't do this - your leader needs to talk to me.

g.title: na9586c5d07c86ba854b293275ba2aba5
g.text: He and I have the same kind of parasite?

g.title: nf69746df58efdfa7a7ce58a451ecac4b
g.text: Seems so. Gave Master Halsin a right start.

g.title: nf5b7e8958ee7c1ba90ee3098ae39e4c2
g.text: We can only hope he succeeded in his mission. Otherwise, that vial's your only option.

g.title: nf75c982059030d20fc53160273b9d2dc
g.text: We can only hope he did. Otherwise you'll need to end things yourself, before the transformation really takes hold.

g.title: nacb76f47ead178162feabf9a548297a4
g.text: Maybe, but it's one hell of a maybe. You could have days or seconds.

g.title: nd9ea89583a09efeb139d59a17e44ae10
g.text: I have important information - the grove will be destroyed without it.

g.title: nfe545687494397fca8b0cbce91ecd829
g.text: The goblins will slaughter you all. Without me, you won't stop them.

g.title: nae2fcc65d0950a613abfd67d2d223e89
g.text: Give me the antidote or I'll tear this place apart.

g.title: nca966dfb01c32c66815036f6b3598c0c
g.text: So you killed him and laid him out on the table?

g.title: nb41ff6f680d23f2b59b43c180166e830
g.text: All right, but on one condition.

g.title: nb7e3d27ca68ddabdf570f5f590c9e1b3
g.text: It's why he joined the adventurers on their expedition. To find out what was happening.

g.title: nbd9e47aa3b0bbb2524e323382eec6ed8
g.text: I don't want to hurt you, but I can't let you live. You're too dangerous.

g.title: nf71bbe9d29242adb795cac3c58c14870
g.text: But the tadpole's dormant - I'm not changing.

g.title: ncf2b908b7ba154900a49349450737a8a
g.text: You don't have to be here for this.

g.title: nd6be9094feea7f34d2b19da8daf9bc47
g.text: If anyone can help you, it'll be him. He studied that tadpole for days and after talking to his birds, he concluded more were infected . He set out to find the source.

g.title: ne4a47ccd2fb8560c54644540d2865e98
g.text: The poison might kill me, but not before I destroy this grove.

g.title: nf460ed69c41f2e7b5b94ed59099e7e66
g.text: You can't do this - your leader needs to talk to me.

g.title: nfec247bf2727f7e81f3cbec4efea2ae9
g.text: But I'm safe - I'm not showing symptoms, and it's been days.

g.title: nf6621824cf45e0f5680569b2cab947b5
g.text: I can't risk you turning. You'd kill us all.
